Ray Schalk was acting manager as McGraw went on a scouting trip.  After losing 3 straight in Chicago, McGraw suddenly announced he must have some new blood on the team and set out in quest of players, although he did not say in which direction he would go.
While warming up Walker, Schalk started arguing with Ump Magerkurth who ejected him.  It was Magerkurth who ejected McGraw in New York.
